# DSAI3202 - Phase 2: Modeling, Validation, and Deployment

## II.1 Model Development

**Problem Type:** Binary Classification (predict match winner)  
**Baseline Model:** Logistic Regression  
**Advanced Models:** Random Forest, Gradient Boosted Trees (GBT)

### Model Justification
| Model | Reason |
|-------|--------|
| Logistic Regression | Simple baseline, interpretable, fast to train |
| Random Forest | Handles non-linear relationships, robust to outliers |
| GBT (selected) | Best performance, handles feature interactions well |

### Training Configuration
- **Train/Test Split:** 80/20 (seed=42 for reproducibility)
- **Training records:** 53,810
- **Testing records:** 13,623
- **Random seed:** 42
- **Framework:** PySpark MLlib on Azure Databricks

---

## II.2 Model Validation

### Evaluation Metrics
| Model | AUC | Accuracy | Precision | Recall | F1 |
|-------|-----|----------|-----------|--------|----|
| Logistic Regression (baseline) | 0.7581 | 68.71% | - | - | - |
| Random Forest | 0.7551 | 69.07% | - | - | - |
| **GBT (best)** | **0.7619** | **69.13%** | **0.6958** | **0.6686** | **0.6819** |

### Confusion Matrix (GBT)
| | Predicted P1 Wins | Predicted P2 Wins |
|---|---|---|
| **Actual P1 Wins** | 4509 (TP) | 2235 (FN) |
| **Actual P2 Wins** | 1971 (FP) | 4908 (TN) |

### Validation Strategy
- Temporal split avoided to prevent data leakage
- 80/20 random split with fixed seed (42)
- Evaluated on held-out test set only
- Compared against logistic regression baseline

### Error Analysis
- Model struggles with close matches (similar rankings)
- Performs well when rank difference is large
- Betting odds are strongest predictor of outcome

---

